<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<topic id="features">
  <title>Features</title>
  <body>
    <section>
      <title>Content Support</title>
      <p>The plugin supports the following content types:</p>
      <table>
        <tgroup cols="3">
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Element</entry>
              <entry>Rendering</entry>
              <entry>Notes</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>topic/title</entry>
              <entry>Google Docs heading (H1-H6)</entry>
              <entry>Depth-based heading levels</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>p</entry>
              <entry>Normal paragraph</entry>
              <entry>With inline formatting</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>codeblock</entry>
              <entry>Monospace text block</entry>
              <entry>Courier New font</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>table</entry>
              <entry>Google Docs table</entry>
              <entry>CALS model support</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>ul/ol</entry>
              <entry>Bulleted/numbered lists</entry>
              <entry>Nested list support</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>dl</entry>
              <entry>Definition list</entry>
              <entry>Bold term, indented definition</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>note</entry>
              <entry>Prefixed callout</entry>
              <entry>Tip, Warning, Important, etc.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>xref</entry>
              <entry>Hyperlink</entry>
              <entry>External links supported</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Authentication Methods</title>
      <p>The plugin supports a cascading authentication strategy:</p>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>gcloud CLI</dt>
          <dd>Uses your existing <codeph>gcloud auth</codeph> session.
          This is the <b>preferred</b> method — no files needed.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>Application Default Credentials</dt>
          <dd>Honors the <codeph>GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS</codeph>
          environment variable or credentials set via
          <codeph>gcloud auth application-default login</codeph>.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>Interactive Login</dt>
          <dd>If gcloud is installed but no session is active, the plugin
          opens a browser for Google sign-in.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>Service Account</dt>
          <dd>For CI/CD pipelines and automated builds. Pass a JSON key
          file with <codeph>--googledoc.credentials</codeph>.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>OAuth 2.0</dt>
          <dd>For interactive local usage with browser consent and
          refresh token persistence.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Configuration Parameters</title>
      <table>
        <tgroup cols="4">
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Parameter</entry>
              <entry>Required</entry>
              <entry>Default</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>googledoc.credentials</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>-</entry>
              <entry>Path to Google credentials JSON file</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>googledoc.auth.type</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>auto</entry>
              <entry>Authentication type: auto, service, or oauth</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>googledoc.doc.id</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>-</entry>
              <entry>Existing document ID to update</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>googledoc.folder.id</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>-</entry>
              <entry>Drive folder ID for new documents</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>googledoc.image.max.width</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>468</entry>
              <entry>Maximum image width in points</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>

    <note type="caution">When using service account authentication, ensure
    the service account has been granted access to the target Google Drive
    folder.</note>
  </body>
</topic>
